		<title>How to Learn the Notes on the Bass Guitar (L#197)</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/beginners/learn-notes-bass-guitar-l197.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/beginners/learn-notes-bass-guitar-l197.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 May 2016 09:16:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Travis Moore]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Beginners]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=14149</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>=== Hey, Scott here... In this lesson I'm going to cover a topic that pretty much everyone struggles with... "How to learn the notes of the neck?!" Don't worry... I had the same issues as you. I struggled to memorise...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/beginners/learn-notes-bass-guitar-l197.html">How to Learn the Notes on the Bass Guitar (L#197)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/7ui66iADgzo" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
<p>===</p>
<p>Hey, Scott here...</p>
<p>In this lesson I'm going to cover a topic that pretty much <em>everyone</em> struggles with...</p>
<p><em>"How to learn the notes of the neck?!"</em></p>
<p>Don't worry... I had the same issues as you.</p>
<p>I struggled to memorise where the notes were, and I also got stuck within the first 5 frets and couldn't seem to move out of that area with confidence.</p>
<p>In this lesson I'm going to show you some great exercises to not only help you memorise the notes of the fingerboard - but also get out of those first 5 frets, with confidence!</p>
<p>I'm also going to tell you exactly what my thought process is when playing grooves or soloing... and weirdly, it's <em>NOT</em> notes... sounds strange, right?</p>
<p>Well, I reveal all in this lesson.</p>
<p><strong>In this lesson you're going to learn:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Why you should start vocalising the note names</li>
<li>How to get out of the "first 5 frets" trap</li>
<li>Using memorised patterns to help with note memorisation</li>
<li>My exact thought process when grooving or soloing on the bass</li>
<li>And as always, way more...</li>
</ul>
<p>Ready? Let's do this!</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed...</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
<p><strong>###</strong></p>
