				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In this lesson I'm going to show you a <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/finger-independence-technique-exercise.html" target="_blank">great exercise</a> that will help you open up your knowledge of the fingerboard and help you play much more freely around the entire instrument.</p>
<p>Before you get rolling with this exercise - <em>take it slowly</em>.</p>
<p>It's not about how fast you can play it, it's about making sure you're playing the <em>correct notes</em>.</p>
<p>Another fantastic thing to add to this exercise is to say the note names out loud as you play them. It's tough - but take it slow and you'll get it!</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed...</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
