		<category><![CDATA[Beginners]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=9988</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>Creating great bass lines is an art form in itself but often gets over shadowed by fancy soloing or slap licks and therefore gets completely over looked by many bass players. I can't stress enough - this is a HUGE...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/danny-mo-morris-r-b-bass-lesson.html">A Masterclass in Bass Line Creation and R&#038;B Bass with Danny Mo Morris</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>Creating great bass lines is an art form in itself but often gets over shadowed by fancy soloing or slap licks and therefore gets completely over looked by many bass players. I can't stress enough - this is a <strong>HUGE</strong> mistake!</p>
<p>Knowing how to create great bass lines and grooves is the bread and butter of <strong>every bass player</strong>. If you don't have this side of your playing happening, the gigs will never come. Period.</p>
<p>In this lesson <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/danny-mo-morris">Danny Mo Morris</a>, one of the longest serving faculty members of the prestigious Berklee college of Music and one of our regular visiting faculty members here at <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-academy">the Academy</a> shows you how to apply arpeggios, chromatic passing tones and much more to create great bass lines and grooves over standard play-along track.</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed…</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
</p>
<p>PS. If you enjoy this lesson and really want to become a great a creating your own bass lines and grooves you should check out Danny's full masterclass, <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/courses/a-masterclass-in-bass-line-creation-and-rb" target="_blank">"<em>A Masterclass in Bass Line Creation and R&amp;B Bass with Danny Mo Morris"</em></a>.</p>
<p>Within the masterclass Danny covers arpeggios, chord tones, scales, how to lock-in with the kick drum and much more, but most importantly - he shows you how to use all of these elements to create awesome bass lines and grooves.</p>
<p>In fact this lesson you're watching is part of Danny's masterclass! :) Check it out and get your FREE 14 day trial <a href="https://www.scottsbasslessons.com/sbl-academy-checkout">HERE</a>.</p>
